<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="348" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1786,2029]" lastBlockId="7.[153,1438,156,435]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="348" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1894,1921]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Eyes uniformly pilose (typical of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stuckenberg" authorityYear="1954" box="[845,1058,1895,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pandasyopthalmus">
<emphasis box="[845,1058,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Pandasyopthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), covered with dense white pile as long as diameter of posterior ocellus and narrowly separated by a length of three ommatidia (
<figureCitation box="[1269,1361,1931,1957]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1648,1673]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,1101,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1437,1101,1623]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Head of male, holotype, frontal view. A Paragus longipilus sp. nov., B Paragus megacercus sp. nov. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842548/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Face with less pronounced tubercle. Spurious vein ends before the meeting point of vein M and the discal cross-vein (
<figureCitation box="[160,249,2002,2029]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1996,2021]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., male, holotype. A lateral view, B dorsal view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842544/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). Tarsi dorsally black, except for yellow meso- and metabasotarsomere, ventrally yellow except for fifth tarsomere (
<figureCitation box="[279,370,156,183]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1996,2021]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., male, holotype. A lateral view, B dorsal view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842544/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Abdomen elongated, about 3 times longer than wide. Tergum 2 with long white pile at lateral margins. Sterna shiny black, covered with long white wavy-tipped pile. In male terminalia, the cerci are enlarged, 5.9 times longer than the narrowest medial part of the epandrium in dorsal view, covered with a short dense and yellow pubescence and very long wavy-tipped yellow pile (
<figureCitation box="[818,889,265,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Figs 6</figureCitation>
A–B). Surstylus small, tapering towards the apex (
<figureCitation box="[161,251,301,328]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Paramere relatively small, dorsal and ventral margins sub-parallel (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1112,301,328]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme large, umbrella-like (
<figureCitation box="[322,412,337,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Based on the shape of its hypandrium, 
<taxonomicName authority="Tot &amp; Radenković &amp; Nedeljković &amp; Likov &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Tot &amp; Radenković &amp; Nedeljković &amp; Likov &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[888,1125,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacercus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[888,1125,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Paragus megacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1135,1227,337,363]" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1135,1227,337,363]" pageId="7" pageNumber="348" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1822" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[153,563,373,399]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haemorrhous">
<emphasis box="[153,403,373,399]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Paragus haemorrhous</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meigen, J. W." box="[408,563,373,399]" pageId="7" pageNumber="348" pagination="22 - 32" refId="ref8145" refString="Meigen, J. W. (1822) Systematische Beschreibung der bekannten europaischen zweiflugeligen Insekten. Dritter Theil, Schulz- Wundermann, Hamm, x + 416 pp. pls. 22 - 32." type="book chapter" year="1822">Meigen, 1822</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[576,659,373,399]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,181,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[224,1364,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male terminalia, lateral view. A, B Paragus marshalli, C, D Paragus dolichocerus, E, F Paragus minutus, G, H Paragus longiventris, I, J Paragus punctatus, K, L Paragus haemorrhous. A, C, E, G, I, K epandrium and hypandrium. B, D, F, H, K, L ejaculatory apodeme. Legend: p, paramera; l, lingula; s, surstylus; ce, cercus. Scale bar, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842554/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="348">Figs 10</figureCitation>
K–L). The enlarged cerci distinguish this species from all other known members of the genus.
</paragraph>
