<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="349" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,444,152,179]" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Description. MALE.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[601,690,153,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="349" unit="mm" value="6.1">6.1 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[847,937,153,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="349" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[949,1011,152,179]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1028,1099,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1996,2021]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., male, holotype. A lateral view, B dorsal view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842544/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Figs 5</figureCitation>
A–B, 7B). Eyes covered with white, uniformly distributed pile, as long as diameter of posterior ocellus; eyes narrowly separated by a length of about three ommatidia (
<figureCitation box="[421,509,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1648,1673]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,1101,1623]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1437,1101,1623]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Head of male, holotype, frontal view. A Paragus longipilus sp. nov., B Paragus megacercus sp. nov. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842548/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
); antenna black; basoflagellomere 2.8 times longer than wide, with rounded apex; arista bare, dark brown; face yellow except black medial vitta extending from the oral margin to the tubercle, dense- ly covered with yellow pile; frontal triangle yellow with yellow pile except for some black pile at the base of lunule; vertical triangle mostly shiny black, but yellowish pollinose anterior to anterior ocellus, covered with predominantly black pile, except yellow pile on the area posterior to ocellar triangle; ocellar triangle equilateral with black pile; occiput narrow, whitish pollinose, covered with yellow pile. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[840,926,404,431]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[943,1010,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1996,2021]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., male, holotype. A lateral view, B dorsal view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842544/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Scutum black, covered with yellow pile; pile just behind the postpronotum yellow, wavy-tipped and longer than pile on the other parts of scutum; scutel- lum covered with yellow pile; pleuron black, whitish pollinose except ventral part of katepisternum; anepisternum and dorsal part of katepisternum with patch of long, dense, white pile; anepimeron with some yellow wavy-tipped pile; wing hyaline, covered with microtrichia, except for some bare areas in cells C, SC, R, BM, CuP and alula; stigma dark brown; spurious vein ending before the meeting point of vein M with discal cross-vein; calypter whit- ish; pedicel of halter brown, capitulum yellow; coxae and trochanters black; femora predominantly yellow, pro- and mesofemora black in basal 1/4; pro- and mesotibiae yellow, metatibia with dark medial ring; tarsi dorsally black, except yellow meso- and metabasotarsomere, ventrally yellow except fifth tarsomere. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1147,1257,692,719]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1275,1345,692,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1996,2021]" captionTargetBox="[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[211,1375,181,1970]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., male, holotype. A lateral view, B dorsal view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842544/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Shiny black, elongated, about 3 times longer than wide; terga black, with white pile on the anterior 1/4 and black adpressed pile on the posterior 3/4; tergum 2 with long white pile on lateral margins; terga 3 and 4 with a pair of poorly visible silver pollinose maculae; sterna shiny black, covered with long white wavy-tipped pile. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1142,1269,800,827]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1285,1354,801,828]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Cerci extraordinarily large, covered with short yellow pubescence and long dense, yellow, wavy-tipped pile (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1366,837,864]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Figs 6</figureCitation>
A–B); surstylus small, tapering to the apex (
<figureCitation box="[562,651,873,900]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); hypandrium on 
<figureCitation box="[845,913,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Figs 6</figureCitation>
C–D; paramere relatively small with sub-paral- lel dorsal and ventral margins (
<figureCitation box="[499,589,909,936]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory apodeme distally with large umbrella-like cap (
<figureCitation box="[1270,1357,909,936]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[153,252,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,466,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[153,1438,456,1858]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Paragus megacercus sp. nov., holotype, male terminalia.A, B epandrium, C, D hypandrium, E ejaculatory apodeme. A, D lateral view, B, E dorsal view, C ventral view. Legend: aa, aedeagal apodeme; ae, aedeagus; ce, cercus; l, lingula; la, lateral lobe of aedeagus; p, paramere; s, surstylus; ss, sperm sac. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3842546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3842546/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1079]" box="[199,451,944,971]" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,944,971]" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">FEMALE.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="349" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,981,1007]" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tot &amp; Radenković &amp; Nedeljković &amp; Likov &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[470,603,982,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megacercus">
<emphasis box="[470,603,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">megacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ (mega is derived from the ancient Greek word ʻ 
<emphasis box="[1160,1232,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="349">megas</emphasis>
ʼ meaning ʻlargeʼ) refers to the extraordinarily large cerci of the male terminalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
